During the blazing Summer months, the best time to go becomes Friday night. It opens at 4pm but most get there around 6pm if they want to shop. Though the number of vendors on Friday night is lower than Sat\/Sun the leased vendors all come out and their selection will be better than Sat\/Sun since it is the first sales day of the week. Also, many more trickle in throughout the night due to the concerts going on via the stage. Because of sunset, the weather is a lot cooler too.

Walk around if you find something you like but is fairly common. A lot of times, many vendors will have the same items and it pays to know the going prices fur things. $3 Blue Rays are common but most pay the market standard of $5 because they don't shop around.

Try checking out the place on Friday night. You want to arrive by 6pm if you are there to shop. The weather is much cooler during the summer and the merchandise selection is strong, though there are a lot fewer vendors than on Sundays. The concert people arrive around 8 and start pouring in. Extremely crowded late night on Fridays.
